<p><strong>Note:</strong> <span class="sc_courseinline"><a href="/search/?P=PHYS%20141" title="PHYS 141" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'PHYS 141');">PHYS 141</a></span> and <span class="sc_courseinline"><a href="/search/?P=PHYS%20142" title="PHYS 142" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'PHYS 142');">PHYS 142</a></span> are offered every semester (including summer session). All other physics courses are offered only in the semester indicated.<br/>
<strong>Note:</strong> Students must earn at least 40 advanced hours at a four-year college or university. These hours may include hours in the major.<br/>
<strong>Note:</strong> The UIC General Education Requirement is nine courses: <span>Two laboratory courses from Analyzing the Natural World, </span><span>one course from each of Understanding the Individual and Society, Understanding the Past, Understanding the Creative Arts, Exploring World Cultures, and Understanding U.S. Society. </span><span>The two remaining General Education courses can be taken from any category. For example, taking <span class="sc_courseinline"><a href="/search/?P=CHEM%20122" title="CHEM 122" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CHEM 122');">CHEM 122</a></span>, <span class="sc_courseinline"><a href="/search/?P=CHEM%20123" title="CHEM 123" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CHEM 123');">CHEM 123</a></span>, <span class="sc_courseinline"><a href="/search/?P=CHEM%20124" title="CHEM 124" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CHEM 124');">CHEM 124</a></span>, <span class="sc_courseinline"><a href="/search/?P=CHEM%20125" title="CHEM 125" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CHEM 125');">CHEM 125</a></span> </span>
<span>and </span><span class="sc_courseinline"><a href="/search/?P=PHYS%20141" title="PHYS 141" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'PHYS 141');">PHYS 141</a></span><span>, </span><span class="sc_courseinline"><a href="/search/?P=PHYS%20142" title="PHYS 142" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'PHYS 142');">PHYS 142</a></span><span> fulfills four of nine General Education courses and the Analyzing the Natural World category.</span></p>
